{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Now it was not a castle fair but I could dream of future there
[D7]Build my castle to the yellow jackets drone
[G]I could orbit round the sun fight with General [C]Washington
[G]Or be a king [D7]upon a golden [G]throne
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
It wasn't fancy built at all we had newspapers on the wall
[D7]It was air-conditioned in the wintertime
[G]Oh it was just an humble hut but its door was never [C]shut
[G]And a man could [D7]get inside without a [G]dime
{end_of_verse}

